 MBOMBELA – The Nelspruit police are urging members of the public who may have fallen victim to robbers or burglars to identify goods and an undisclosed sum of money. A Divergent Ops security officer noticed a man acting suspiciously at about 04:45 near Crossing Centre in Mbombela this morning. The recovered cash. ALSO READ: Stage 2 load-shedding for Wednesday He gave chase and the suspect fled before discarding a backpack he was carrying. The officer examined the contents of the bag and discovered a camera, binoculars and an undisclosed amount of cash. The abandoned stash included a bag filled with coins. No arrests have been made and police are urging any victims to come forward. The goods will be returned after  positive identification.